Female. Body more convex and more oval than in male. Interantennal space 1.85 times as wide as transverse diameter of antennal socket. Interocular space 2.15 time as wide as transverse diameter of eye. Antenna 0.65 times as long as body. Last ventrite transverse, widely rounded (
Fig. 69
). Pygidium subtriangular with rounded apex (
Fig. 68
). Protarsomere I and mesotarsomere I narrower than in males. Sternite VIII subtriangular with anterior margin widely rounded, tignum slender, twice longer than sternite VIII (
Fig. 66
). Spermatheca: nodulus gradually continuing to cornu, cornu widely C-shaped, proximal spermathecal duct wide basally, almost straight and than abruptly narrowed (
Fig. 65
